When the experiment was thought to be concluded, 
I left the lab for sometime. I had in mind that
most of the oxygen would surely be consumed once
the system could be restrained into different 
modulated parts. As far as the evolution went, 
things looked stagger. Conclusions couldn't really
be put into place. Untill some passing, the bloom
began to appear as an unexpected fusion of organic
and cyber matter. Modded and reloaded, injection
permeated the agressive takeover, and pretty soon
began to show itself as a new species. Beyond expectations, 
the emanation was around 7745.2 mhz, and measurements
could not fit the patterns. Untill then, reporting back.
